1
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:24,420
♪It's a sordid story that you've made♪

2
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:32,700
♪Up to fill my mind with doubts and pain♪

3
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:40,220
♪Blood I shed, and tears I wept,
are you satisfied?♪

4
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:42,540
♪Enjoying what's mine♪

5
00:00:42,540 --> 00:00:49,500
♪Have you found a way
to bury guilt and shame♪

6
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:55,020
♪I'm coming back to life♪

7
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Through the seven gates of death♪

8
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,820
♪I'm coming back survived♪

9
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:06,580
♪Feeling great to see you fall♪

10
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:10,820
♪I'm taking back what's mine♪

11
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,340
♪Bringing horror to the battlefield♪

12
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:19,060
♪Lay it to waste♪

13
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,940
♪Til the day my kingdom is reclaimed♪

14
00:01:38,260 --> 00:01:42,540
=Her Blaze=

15
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:46,020
=Episode 10=

16
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:56,239
Mr. Jiang, you were looking for me?

17
00:02:03,879 --> 00:02:07,680
I heard Investment Dept 3
is doing incredibly well.

18
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,199
It's all thanks to you.

19
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,159
Prepare the invitations
for the Boundary Forum.

20
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,759
Have Investment Dept 3 attend as well.

21
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,360
I want to reward them.

22
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:15,560
Go on.

23
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:18,000
Mr. Jiang, there's a call for you.

24
00:02:18,199 --> 00:02:19,240
Tell them I'm busy.

25
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:21,879
It's Ms. Bai calling.

26
00:02:35,479 --> 00:02:36,280
Ms. Bai,

27
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:37,520
long time no see.

28
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,080
Come, come.

29
00:02:39,740 --> 00:02:41,280
You're still looking as healthy as ever.

30
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,199
Liangliang.

31
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:51,919
Come in.

32
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,240
Mr. Jiang.

33
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,400
Why are you standing?

34
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,000
Have a seat.

35
00:03:10,599 --> 00:03:11,439
You may leave.

36
00:03:33,879 --> 00:03:36,800
Ms. Bai, is there something you want to say?

37
00:03:41,479 --> 00:03:42,400
When people get old,

38
00:03:42,919 --> 00:03:44,400
they need to learn two things.

39
00:03:46,319 --> 00:03:48,319
Do more work and talk less.

40
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,280
If an old lady

41
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,400
talks too much,

42
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:56,120
she'll only be disliked.

43
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,599
Liangliang,

44
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,879
go get me another bowl of soup.

45
00:04:07,420 --> 00:04:09,360
I don't want those
old pork ribs inside anymore.

46
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,680
Back in university,

47
00:04:15,719 --> 00:04:17,720
you were the mentor
who helped me the most.

48
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,519
Did I do something wrong

49
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,759
to make you dissatisfied?

50
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:22,439
How could that be?

51
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,959
You are my most valued student.

52
00:04:28,639 --> 00:04:29,680
Otherwise, back then,

53
00:04:29,879 --> 00:04:31,639
I wouldn't have given the school's

54
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:33,439
last spot for studying abroad

55
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:34,560
to you.

56
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,199
I'm deeply grateful.

57
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,360
Tell me, every time you faced a hardship,

58
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,279
wasn't it the Bai family
that jumped out first

59
00:04:49,279 --> 00:04:50,240
to support you?

60
00:04:53,839 --> 00:04:56,360
So I'll give you a piece of advice.

61
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,399
Don't become an old rib.

62
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:05,680
Otherwise, you'll be
discarded at any moment.

63
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,120
Thank you for the reminder, Ms. Bai.

64
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,759
Ms. Bai, please have some tea.

65
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,240
Since it's tea from Mr. Jiang,

66
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,720
hurry up and drink it.

67
00:05:47,199 --> 00:05:48,279
Thank you, Mr. Jiang.

68
00:05:57,959 --> 00:05:58,959
Thank you, Grandma.

69
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:10,040
The environmental protection industry?

70
00:06:10,279 --> 00:06:11,399
This has never been

71
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:13,199
a field that Bosi is interested in.

72
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,560
Look, we all know

73
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,720
these numbers.

74
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,240
But when real estate
pivots to environmental protection,

75
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:22,759
at most it's just using
some eco-friendly materials

76
00:06:22,759 --> 00:06:24,000
to save a bit of money.

77
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,480
Compared to seizing and selling land,

78
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,100
the profit doesn't even come close.

79
00:06:28,879 --> 00:06:29,680
Right?

80
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,519
Right.

81
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,120
Whatever you say is right, Miss Meng.

82
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:36,279
What if we discuss
the volume of this profit

83
00:06:37,439 --> 00:06:39,160
at a city-wide scale?

84
00:06:39,639 --> 00:06:40,439
The city?

85
00:06:41,759 --> 00:06:42,560
Tian Tian.

86
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,879
(Renovation of existing buildings)
Take a look at this.

87
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:50,839
This here

88
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:51,879
is some data

89
00:06:51,879 --> 00:06:53,240
that Yuci and I gathered.

90
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,120
As of the end of last year,

91
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:57,839
the total amount of old housing
built before the year 2000

92
00:06:57,839 --> 00:06:58,680
already exceeded

93
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,120
220 million square meters.

94
00:07:00,319 --> 00:07:01,199
Its proportion

95
00:07:01,199 --> 00:07:03,040
among residential housing in the city

96
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:03,959
has already exceeded

97
00:07:03,959 --> 00:07:05,040
30 percent.

98
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,279
Now,

99
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:07,160
most of these buildings

100
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,319
are very old and non-eco-friendly,

101
00:07:09,319 --> 00:07:11,160
and they consume
a massive amount of energy.

102
00:07:11,519 --> 00:07:12,160
So,

103
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,680
for the Linwei Alley Urban Project,

104
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:14,439
from the outside,

105
00:07:14,439 --> 00:07:15,920
it might look like

106
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:17,560
Yang Jinwan's previous

107
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,160
land-buying and leasing model.

108
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,759
But what it actually cares about more

109
00:07:23,519 --> 00:07:24,480
is the business of

110
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,199
renovating our existing housing stock.

111
00:07:26,199 --> 00:07:26,980
(What does the renovation
of existing buildings mainly involve?)

112
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,199
Wait a minute.

113
00:07:32,399 --> 00:07:33,959
Boss, can I interpret this to mean

114
00:07:33,959 --> 00:07:35,360
that Yang Jinwan never actually

115
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:37,000
wanted this land from the start?

116
00:07:41,199 --> 00:07:42,800
Do you know how much

117
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,680
the total renovation area

118
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,760
for existing housing
in the whole country is?

119
00:07:45,959 --> 00:07:46,759
No idea.

120
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,959
(The market for existing housing renovation is huge)
4 billion square meters.

121
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:55,560
If we calculate it at a minimum standard

122
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,600
of 200 yuan per square meter,

123
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,500
how much money is that?

124
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,360
800, I guess.

125
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,600
How much?

126
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:03,839
8,000.

127
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,959
Why don't you just retire?

128
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,079
What a genius.

129
00:08:09,079 --> 00:08:10,399
So no matter who buys it,

130
00:08:10,759 --> 00:08:11,920
they'll have to renovate.

131
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,390
What Yang Jinwan is after
is exactly this lucrative piece of meat.

132
00:08:14,439 --> 00:08:15,959
Do you still think he's a joke?

133
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,920
I am. I'm the joke.

134
00:08:21,540 --> 00:08:24,540
(The country has 160,000 old residential communities,
with an area of about 4 billion sqm.)

135
00:08:47,399 --> 00:08:48,759
Ms. Chen, Mr. Jiang...

136
00:08:55,679 --> 00:08:56,639
You halted my project,

137
00:08:56,639 --> 00:08:57,480
Mr. Jiang.

138
00:08:57,700 --> 00:08:59,680
Is sending me flowers
supposed to be an apology?

139
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:02,200
Flowers?

140
00:09:03,039 --> 00:09:03,840
What flowers?

141
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,840
The flowers were from me.

142
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,600
Do you like them, Ms. Chen?

143
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:17,840
After some adjustments,

144
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,519
Ms. Bai is now ready to return to work.

145
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:21,639
I still have to thank Mr. Jiang

146
00:09:21,639 --> 00:09:22,879
for teaching me a lesson.

147
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,159
It was very useful,

148
00:09:24,559 --> 00:09:27,559
especially regarding anger management.

149
00:09:27,799 --> 00:09:29,120
You should try it too, Ms. Chen.

150
00:09:33,879 --> 00:09:35,320
You are quite something, Ms. Bai.

151
00:09:36,039 --> 00:09:37,639
Despite all of Mr. Jiang's precautions,

152
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,200
you still managed to come back.

153
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:40,120
You and I

154
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:42,000
have never been in competition,

155
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:43,399
let alone enemies.

156
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,480
However, this time, Mr. Jiang

157
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,600
really did you wrong.

158
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,480
From now on,

159
00:09:50,679 --> 00:09:52,200
we have one and only one

160
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,399
common enemy,

161
00:09:53,639 --> 00:09:54,679
Rao Yuci.

162
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,919
I will definitely cooperate with you.

163
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:12,340
(Tian Tian: Yuci, Bai Liangliang is back.
She's still in Dept 1.)

164
00:10:12,340 --> 00:10:15,060
(Rao Yuci: Understood.)

165
00:10:28,559 --> 00:10:29,600
(As I expected.)

166
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,679
(Through Bai Muran's grandmother,)

167
00:10:31,679 --> 00:10:33,320
(you've returned
to your original position.)

168
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:35,159
(I've returned to my original position.)

169
00:10:35,519 --> 00:10:38,159
(I want to take back
my say in Lysen Group.)

170
00:10:38,639 --> 00:10:39,399
(You think)

171
00:10:39,399 --> 00:10:40,919
(you have a lot of influence,)

172
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,600
(but in Jiang Dongchao's heart,)

173
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,360
(you're just a foolish oriole.)

174
00:10:44,679 --> 00:10:45,639
(Although I lost)

175
00:10:45,639 --> 00:10:47,080
(Jiang Dongchao's trust,)

176
00:10:47,559 --> 00:10:48,879
(I still have people)

177
00:10:49,039 --> 00:10:51,000
(under my control.)

178
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:53,039
(Bai Liangliang,)

179
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:54,879
(you will soon)

180
00:10:54,879 --> 00:10:56,519
(pay a new price.)

181
00:11:02,399 --> 00:11:04,500
Mr. Jiang is now
letting us take over this project.

182
00:11:06,679 --> 00:11:07,960
Do you have any thoughts?

183
00:11:17,679 --> 00:11:18,720
I think

184
00:11:19,879 --> 00:11:20,600
an established

185
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,360
real estate company like Bosi

186
00:11:22,799 --> 00:11:24,600
will definitely
offer better terms than we do.

187
00:11:25,399 --> 00:11:26,919
So, these building material companies

188
00:11:26,919 --> 00:11:27,919
basically

189
00:11:28,279 --> 00:11:30,200
have no reason to choose us.

190
00:11:31,679 --> 00:11:32,600
The terms Bosi offers

191
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,799
might not be better than ours.

192
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,679
Bosi's current cash flow

193
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,000
is quite unstable.

194
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:41,120
Some of their money

195
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,320
is tied up in land.

196
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:43,600
So when they acquire

197
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:44,919
these building material companies,

198
00:11:44,919 --> 00:11:46,759
they will definitely play the bully.

199
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:48,799
The acquisition terms
will be very harsh.

200
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:50,780
(Rao Yuci)

201
00:11:51,279 --> 00:11:52,080
But

202
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,480
we were talking to Bosi first.

203
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,320
We know.

204
00:11:54,919 --> 00:11:56,320
But I think you also understand

205
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:58,639
that Bosi's acquisition condition
is to dismiss half

206
00:11:58,639 --> 00:12:00,000
of your employees, right?

207
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,720
These are all of them, right?

208
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:10,360
Mr. Wang.

209
00:12:10,679 --> 00:12:11,159
Hello.

210
00:12:11,159 --> 00:12:12,240
Welcome. Come on in.

211
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,440
Please have a seat.

212
00:12:14,919 --> 00:12:16,360
I've read

213
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,559
many of the reports.

214
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:20,200
Few companies write

215
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,559
their data so meticulously.

216
00:12:21,639 --> 00:12:23,120
I always thought

217
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:25,440
Lysen and Bosi

218
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:27,480
were equally harsh and arrogant.

219
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,559
I feel that these companies

220
00:12:31,559 --> 00:12:32,720
are quite conflicted.

221
00:12:33,879 --> 00:12:35,679
If they sell,

222
00:12:35,919 --> 00:12:37,240
they fear losing control.

223
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:38,639
If they don't,

224
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:40,600
they fear the market being monopolized.

225
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:42,960
I'm thinking,

226
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,279
what if we try to

227
00:12:46,559 --> 00:12:47,279
give

228
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:48,720
these companies enough security?

229
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:49,720
Help them escape

230
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:50,840
that wolf, Yang Jinwan.

231
00:12:51,559 --> 00:12:52,480
Then, the scales

232
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,320
will tip toward Lysen.

233
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:55,960
Lysen guarantees

234
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:58,390
that we will absolutely not dismiss
your employees.

235
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,159
We are only responsible

236
00:13:00,679 --> 00:13:02,320
for matters in our investment field.

237
00:13:02,380 --> 00:13:03,679
This is how we achieve a win-win.

238
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:05,320
So, Mr. Wang,

239
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:06,559
Lysen Group

240
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,559
hopes for

241
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:08,879
excellent partners,

242
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,200
not enemies.

243
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,799
Giving our partners

244
00:13:11,799 --> 00:13:13,000
full security

245
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,159
is Lysen Group's constant
original intention.

246
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,840
The business investigation report
must be detailed.

247
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:20,559
Market data integration
must be accurate.

248
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:23,000
This is what we must do
for these companies.

249
00:13:23,350 --> 00:13:24,440
Just like when we were doing

250
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,159
the Linwei Alley
Snack Street Renewal Plan.

251
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,600
From personnel allocation

252
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:28,799
(Jinhai Jincheng Green Building Materials Co., Ltd.)
to future development,

253
00:13:28,919 --> 00:13:30,759
(Jinhai Dongfeng Green Building Materials Co., Ltd.)
we must give them enough confidence.

254
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:32,840
(Hangdong Qixing Green Building Materials Co., Ltd.)
Bosi is a real estate company.

255
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:35,320
(Liangang Qinli Building Materials Co., Ltd.)
They might not collect data as well as we do.

256
00:13:35,559 --> 00:13:36,559
(Nanwu Weifeng Building Materials Co., Ltd.)
This is also

257
00:13:36,559 --> 00:13:37,759
(Nanwu Long'aotian Building Materials Co., Ltd.)
the key factor

258
00:13:38,039 --> 00:13:39,159
(Jinhai Fengrao Green Building Materials Co., Ltd.)
in their decision to choose Lysen.

259
00:13:39,159 --> 00:13:41,720
(Linhai Chunfeng Building Materials Co., Ltd.,
Yinzhou Shengjing Green Building Materials Co., Ltd.)

260
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,440
And also engineering equipment.

261
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,039
Right.

262
00:13:44,039 --> 00:13:44,679
Okay.

263
00:13:56,879 --> 00:13:57,759
I think you

264
00:13:57,759 --> 00:13:58,759
can ask Mr. Jiang

265
00:13:58,759 --> 00:14:00,399
for a fair chance.

266
00:14:02,559 --> 00:14:04,039
I will definitely cooperate with you.

267
00:14:17,759 --> 00:14:19,000
Didn't I let you off work?

268
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,159
It's so late.

269
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,440
Aren't you hungry, Mr. Jiang?

270
00:14:27,559 --> 00:14:28,639
Let's eat together.

271
00:14:54,639 --> 00:14:55,399
This was originally

272
00:14:55,399 --> 00:14:56,799
our Dept 3's project.

273
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,559
What's with Dept 2

274
00:14:58,559 --> 00:14:59,919
butting in like this?

275
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:02,480
What if we fail?

276
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,639
How could we fail?

277
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,960
We've prepared so thoroughly.

278
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:07,840
What's wrong?

279
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:09,159
Yuci.

280
